metadata.name: Bob Dylan on Billboard 200 - Vinyl Style
metadata.description:
This artwork, created from real data, visualizes the number of weeks Bob Dylan's albums stayed on the Billboard 200 and the peak position that they reached. Black-colored radial bars show the number of weeks for which each album remained on the Billboard 200, and red-colored radial bars show the peak position that each album reached. Text next to each black-colored bar indicates the album's name and songs from that album.

The buyer will be able to download the digital file in png format. file dimensions are 5400x7200 pixels.
